    "summary": "This paper studies the strongly correlated Weyl-Kondo semimetal Ce3Bi4Pd3 and shows that magnetic field can continuously suppress its topological response, ultimately annihilating the Weyl nodes at about 9 T while leaving the Kondo-correlated background intact. A second field scale near 13.8 T marks a Kondo-insulator-to-heavy-fermion-metal transition, supported by Hall, resistivity, torque, and specific-heat measurements.",
